    ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯                                       ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
Welcome to AmiChannel News

Hello and welcome to the 13th issue of AmiChannel News.

I  do  not  know why, but summer use to be a time for convulsion. Days after the
release  of  the  June  issue of the magazine you are reading, Amiga dropped the
bomb  again.  Not  QNX,  but  Linux  is  going to be the OS kernel for the Amiga
Operative Environment (also known as Amiga OE).

Actually,  the  bomb was dropped by QNX themself when they announced the release
of  his  own  operating  system  (QNX  Neutrino)  for  the current Amiga line of
computers.  So,  Amiga (I mean Jim Collas) had to release a note very quickly to
notify that Linux was going to be the OS kernel.

People like Fleecy Moss, Dave Haynie and Holger Kruse have pointed out that this
decision  is  not the correct one. Other people have disagreed with the election
but  they  have  not  raised any valid technical reason (I will not say any name
because they suck).

Sometimes,  I can not understand this Amiga "community" (if it does exists). Jim
Collas has saved the classic Amiga and he wants to release a new platform with a
modern  operating  environment. And because they take a decision some people are
against  for,  they  complain.  Perhaps  this  is  the key word for some people.
Complain. Complain about everything. And if they can not, they explode. So, I am
asking  you  to  be patient and not overreact like others. Give Amiga a break to
explain everything. Then decide for yourself.

Linux has his disadvantages. Of course, it is not the perfect OS, becuase it has
some technical issues which have to be solved. But QNX has its own disadvantages
For instance, support of BIG names.

Amiga  has  not  chosen  Linux  because  they want people to complain. They have
selected  Linux  because  with  it we have some chance to succeed. For instance,
Corel  has  announced  their  support  for  the  Amiga  NG,  that  is, the Amiga
Multimedia  Convergence  Computer  (Amiga MCC, MCC = 1200 in roman numbers). So,
you can expect a wordprocessor like WordPerfect for the new Amiga.

Another  reason  is  the  chip.  It is not official but Transmeta is the Monster
Mistery Chip. Intentional or by mistake, Amiga showed a video in this year World
of Amiga and Amiwest, with the Transmeta name clearly displayed on the screen.

But  the  controversy  does  not  end here. Phase 5 have announced that their G3
boards,  along  with  their  new multimedia computer AmiRage K2, are going to be
powered  by  the  QNX Newtrino OS, so do not expect that your legacy software is
going  to  be  run in the Phase 5 boards. Anyway, they are doing their business.
So, good luck to them

Let  me  to  finnish this editorial to announce that there is not going to be an
August  issue  of this e-magazine, because I am leaving for my holidays. So, see
you in September.

Remember to visit the SAUG website, which is located in:

         http://www.saug.com/

or you can visit its mirrors located in:

         http://www.geocities.com/SiliconValley/Drive/1045/saug.html

And if you want to contribute to this effort, you can send your articles to:

         angel@saug.org

Thanks for reading and I hope you enjoy this issue.

===============================================================================
Angel Alvarez Díaz - angel@saug.org
Editor of the e-magazine AmiChannel News.
Responsible of the News Departament of S.A.U.G and Amiga Channel.
Member of C.U.A.E Nº 293 - FOREIGN DIRECTOR
