           THE NEW DEVELOPMENTS OF ACTIVE TECHNOLOGIES/VAPOR SOFTWARE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Active  Tecnologies  have  released  some  information about their new products,
which  will  be shown (and perhaps sell, depending on the development status) at
the WOA (www.worldofamiga.com) this year. They include:

   * STFax  4  - this will be a CD only based product containing a number of new
     features,  existing  feature  updates  and  over 60 professionally recorded
     voice  messages.  They have re-written the fax on demand system, re-written
     remote  access,  created  a  new  status  window,  added  features  such as
     'auto-warn',  'auto-forwarding  of  faxes', 'fax filtering', re-written the
     mini-BBS and many other small changes.

   * NetConnect  3  -  This is goint to be a bigger update than NetConnect 2 was
     for  v1  users.  New/updated  programs include Voyager 3, AmIRC 3, mFTP II,
     AmChat,  NetInfo  II, AmTelnet 2 and more. they will also include a WYSIWYG
     web editor.

   * New  Vapor  software - as well as Voyager 3 and AmIRC 3, there will also be
     mFTP II, Octopus and the WYSIWYG editor on show or launched at the show.

All existing Vapor software will be a available for purchase at the show.
