                   CONTENTS OF THE ISSUE 127 OF AMIGA FORMAT
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

These  are  the  contents  of the 127th issue of Amiga Format to be on sale July
30th.

Features
   * QNX vs. Linux - We bring you the latest news on the shock decision by Amiga
     to  switch from the well-liked RTOS to what some see as a boring monolithic
     OS  as  the new kernel. (Note: The full transcripts for the interviews will
     be  posed on the main AFB list as soon as this issue is available, and will
     also be present on the CD and floppies for next issue)
   * The  Art  of  Noise  - Tony Horgan gives you all the details you'll need to
     make your own record and get it in the shops.
   * The  Right  Type - Richard Drummond explains all you need to know about the
     Amiga's font system.
   * ImageFX  4  Work  in Progress - Kermit Woodall leads us through more of the
     new  and  groovy  features  in  this  new  version of the outstanding image
     processing package.

Reviews
   * Arizona  -  Pat  McDonald  gets  one of these brilliant video mixers in for
     review.
   * Kodak  DC200+  -  Simon  Goodwin  examines his latest purchase and finds it
     good.
   * Power  Tower  A4000  -  I  know  you've  all been waiting for this one, and
     Richard Drummond has it for test in this issue...
