@node not24 "FUBAR NEWS"

                                   FUBAR NEWS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Andrew  King  (bartman@rosande.nu)  of  Rosande  Limited,  developers of the war
strategy  game  FUBAR,  has informed us that the 2nd alpha of the game is just a
few days away, so I'd better tell you what you can expect from it.

The main news of the development of FUBAR is that FUDGE is complete. In case you
don't  know  what  FUDGE  is,  it  (FUbar  Development  enGinE) is a programming
language which allows anyone to program a 2D game using the FUBAR engine.

The  good  news  is that it is complete. Documentation for it though is a little
thin on the ground at the moment, but this is due to be resolved very soon.

As  FUBAR now can read and execute FUDGE object code, you can compile sources in
FUDGE and then pass them over to FUBAR for execution. And it's pretty quick too,
since it's compiled and not interepreted (like AMOS for example).

An alpha version is currently available. More info at www.rosande.nu
