fully  memory-protected  application under the Neutrino kernel. A new version of
the   PPC   library  will  provide  full  compatibility  with  existing  PowerPC
applications  which  make use of the message system of the PPC library, and call
threads  under  the  QNX  Neutrino  OS  to  execute the PowerPC code. Similarly,
updated  drivers  for  CyberGraphX  and  the CyberSCSI device will directly call
native GFX and SCSI drivers under the QNX Neutrino OS, thus providing native PPC
execution and increased stability with full memory protection again. By this new
software  implementation,  the  current PowerUP© Accelerator boards will provide
increased  performance  and usability for many applications, and will also serve
as  development  systems  for  software  developers writing applications for the
AMIRAGE©  K2  next-generation  multimedia  computer  systems  by phase 5 digital
products, which will be running the QNX Neutrino OS.

The  new  QNX  Neutrino  OS for PowerUP© and next-generation multimedia computer
systems,  including  the  Amiga® OS 3.x / 68k emulation system, will be shipping
with  the  new  Blizzard and Cyberstorm G3 Accelerators, which are scheduled for
delivery  by  end  of September 99. For all users of the installed 603/604 based
PowerUP©  boards,  the  complete software package will be available for free via
internet download, or on CD against a fee covering handling and postage.

With  an installed base of appx. 10,000 systems, the PowerUP© accelerators today
represent  a  small,  but  very  respectable starting base for all active Amiga®
developers  to port and update their applications to the new QNX Neutrino OS for
PowerUP©,  and improve them with new functionality. With the new next-generation
multimedia  computer  systems,  a rapidly growing market for innovative software
developers  will  emerge  early  in  the  year 2000. phase 5 digital products is
strongly  encouraging developers to port applications to the new QNX Neutrino OS
for  PowerUP©  and  next-generation multimedia computer systems. A new developer
contact at phase 5 digital products will be installed by end of August 99.
