@node not28 "QNX AND PHASE 5 TEAM UP TO PROVIDE MIGRATION PATH FOR AMIGA USERS"

       QNX AND PHASE 5 TEAM UP TO PROVIDE MIGRATION PATH FOR AMIGA USERS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Kanata, Canada and Oberursel, Germany - July 22, 1999 - QNX Software Systems and
phase  5 digital products have announced a licensing agreement that allows phase
5  to port the QNX Neutrino OS to its current line of PowerUPTM accelerators for
Amiga computers.

Once  the  port is completed, the two companies will donate a runtime version of
the  OS  free  of  charge  to  the Amiga community. This version will run on all
current 603/604-based PowerUP boards.

"By  teaming  up  with  the  leading manufacturer of hardware upgrades for Amiga
computers,  we're  taking  the  next step in our growing commitment to the Amiga
community,"  said  Dan  Dodge,  CTO  at QNX Software Systems. "More importantly,
Amiga  developers  will  benefit in at least two ways. First, they can use their
existing  Amiga  computers  to  develop  next-generation multimedia applications
based  on  the  QNX  Neutrino OS. QNX application development will be completely
self-hosted;   no  PCs  required.  Second,  they  can  run  their  legacy  Amiga
applications  and  new QNX applications simultaneously, thanks to a powerful 68k
emulator from phase 5, which will provide Amiga OS 3.x support."

"QNX  provides  all  the  software  functionality  -  and  more - to fulfill the
expectations of the many users who still believe in the original Amiga vision: a
vision  of  technical  superiority,  innovation,  and just plain fun," said Wolf
Dietrich,  general  manager  of  phase 5 digital products. "By putting all these
features, OS services, and tools straight into the hands of Amiga developers, we
expect  that a large number of applications running under QNX for PowerUP boards
will be released quickly."

Phase  5  also has the option to license QNX for future standalone systems based
on next-generation PowerPC processors.

Availability  The  QNX  Neutrino  OS for PowerUP boards, including applications,
windowing  system,  drivers,  and Amiga 68k emulation system, will ship with the
new  phase  5  Blizzard  and Cyberstorm G3 accelerators, which are scheduled for
delivery in Fall 99.

For  users  of  current 603/604-based PowerUP boards, the ported runtime package
will be available for free download via the Internet, or on CD for a nominal fee
(to cover handling and postage).

About QNX Software Systems

Founded  in  1980,  QNX  Software  Systems  is  the industry leader in realtime,
microkernel OS technology. The company has established a strong customer base in
a  variety  of  industries,  including consumer electronics, telecommunications,
aerospace,   medical   instrumentation,   process  control,  point-of-sale,  and
telephony.  QNX  products are distributed in over 100 countries worldwide. Visit
www.qnx.com.

About phase 5 digital products

Phase  5  digital  products,  located in Oberursel near Frankfurt, Germany, is a
privately  held  hardware design and manufacturing company, founded in 1992. The
company  started  as a hardware developer and manufacturer of Amiga add-ons, and
by  the  mid-90s became the leading vendor of accelerators, graphics boards, and
SCSI  controllers  for  the  Amiga  platform.  Since  1996, the company has been
expanding  into  the Macintosh add-on market and has become recognized worldwide
as a manufacturer of upgrade products for PowerMacs and compatibles. Phase 5 has
shipped  more  than  100,000 hardware upgrades, and received more than two dozen
product of the year awards. Visit www.phase5.de.
